  "title": "Zero-Sum Capacity Split",
  "concept": "When a system splits capacity between two goals, pushing one higher forces the other lower — you choose the balance, but total capacity stays fixed.",
  "interactiveId": "a7dfaf4c-8279-48d3-b419-05bff1132f34",
  "sourcePieceId": "62ae4989-cea9-4abc-8696-f554cd78ad95",
